(52, 4, 'EX', 'California has a zero-tolerance policy towards underage drinking and driving. If your BAC was less than 0.08%, you may receive an infraction, which means the maximum penalty is a fine. You may also lose your driver&#039;s license for up to a year. If your BAC was 0.08% or greater, you may be charged with a normal DUI.', 'Under 21', 2, 'Continue,,', '', 0),
